Sentencas: K2NiF4-type structure oxides La2Cu1-xCoxO4 (x = 0.1, 0.2, 0.3) are synthesized and evaluated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The materials are characterized by XRD, SEM and electrochemical impedance spectrum (EIS), respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The results show that no reaction occurs between La2Cu1-xCoxO4 electrode and Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) electrolyte at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrode forms good contact with the electrolyte after sintering at 800 degrees C for 4 h in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrode properties of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 are studied under various temperatures and oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The optimum composition of La2Cu0.8Co0.2O4 results in 0.51 Omega cm(2) polarization resistance (R-p) at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The rate limiting step for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) is the charge transfer process.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: La2Cu0.8Co0.2O4 cathode exhibits the lowest overpotential of about 50 mV at a current density of 48 mA cm(-2) at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La2Cu1-xCoxO4 cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs
